"title": "7328: ceremonies",
"media_type": "Text",
"index_reference": "7328",
"language": "eng",
"review_level": "None",
"content": "<p>Formal outward practices and rituals symbolising or marking events of importance or spiritual significance. Although they had their place in biblical cultural life, they may become empty and hypocritical, losing their deep spiritual meaning. Ceremonies thus become symbolic of empty legalism which should be rejected.</p>\n<h2>Ceremonies marking important events</h2>\n<h3>Different stages in life</h3>\n<p><a href=\"https://ref.ly/Gen50:7\">GEN 50:7</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Gen50:10-Gen50:11\">GEN 50:10–50:11</a>; ; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Exod13:2\">EXO 13:2</a>; ; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Judg14:10\">JDG 14:10</a>; ; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Jer34:5\">JER 34:5</a>; ; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/John2:1-John2:2\">JHN 2:1–2:2</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/John20:4\">JHN 20:4</a></p>\n<h3>Temple worship</h3>\n<p><strong><a href=\"https://ref.ly/Neh13:9\">NEH 13:9</a></strong> <em>See also</em> <a href=\"https://ref.ly/1Kgs9:25\">1KI 9:25</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/1Chr16:40\">1CH 16:40</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/2Chr8:13\">2CH 8:13</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/2Chr29:15\">2CH 29:15</a>PSA <a href=\"https://ref.ly/2Chr5:7\">5:7</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Ps118:19-Ps118:20\">PSA 118:19–118:20</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Ps138:2\">PSA 138:2</a>\n<a href=\"https://ref.ly/Acts3:1\">ACT 3:1</a></p>\n<h3>Appointing leaders</h3>\n<p><strong><a href=\"https://ref.ly/Acts13:2-Acts13:3\">ACT 13:2–13:3</a></strong> <em>See also</em> <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Lev8:30\">LEV 8:30</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/1Sam16:13\">1SA 16:13</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/1Kgs1:39\">1KI 1:39</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Acts6:5-Acts6:6\">ACT 6:5–6:6</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Acts9:17\">ACT 9:17</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/1Tim4:14\">1TI 4:14</a></p>\n<h3>Historical events</h3>\n<p><strong><a href=\"https://ref.ly/Ruth4:7-Ruth4:8\">RUT 4:7–4:8</a></strong> <em>See also</em> <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Gen35:14\">GEN 35:14</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Exod12:14\">EXO 12:14</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Exod13:9\">EXO 13:9</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Josh4:4-Josh4:9\">JOS 4:4–4:9</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/1Sam7:12\">1SA 7:12</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Luke22:19\">LUK 22:19</a> parallel <a href=\"https://ref.ly/1Cor11:24-1Cor11:25\">1CO 11:24–11:25</a></p>\n<h2>Ceremonies as spiritual symbols of God's presence</h2>\n<p><strong><a href=\"https://ref.ly/Matt18:20\">MAT 18:20</a></strong> <em>There is a sense in which any gathering of believers is ceremonially symbolic of God's presence.</em> <em>See also</em> <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Exod30:25-Exod30:29\">EXO 30:25–30:29</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Num4:4\">NUM 4:4</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Num10:35-Num10:36\">NUM 10:35–10:36</a> <em>The ark of the covenant was a symbol of God's presence among his people. It, and its location, the tabernacle and later, the Most Holy Place, were therefore centres of the most elaborate ceremonies</em>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/1Kgs8:3-1Kgs8:6\">1KI 8:3–8:6</a> parallel <a href=\"https://ref.ly/2Chr5:4-2Chr5:7\">2CH 5:4–5:7</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/1Kgs8:29\">1KI 8:29</a> parallel <a href=\"https://ref.ly/2Chr6:20\">2CH 6:20</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/1Chr6:49\">1CH 6:49</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Heb9:1-Heb9:7\">HEB 9:1–9:7</a></p>\n<h2>Initiation ceremonies</h2>\n<h3>Circumcision</h3>\n<p><strong><a href=\"https://ref.ly/Lev12:3\">LEV 12:3</a></strong> <em>See also</em> <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Gen17:10\">GEN 17:10</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Josh5:2\">JOS 5:2</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Luke2:21-Luke2:24\">LUK 2:21–2:24</a></p>\n<h3>Baptism</h3>\n<p><strong><a href=\"https://ref.ly/Matt28:19\">MAT 28:19</a></strong> <em>See also</em> <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Acts2:38\">ACT 2:38</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Acts16:33-Acts16:34\">ACT 16:33–16:34</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/1Pet3:21\">1PE 3:21</a></p>\n<h2>Ceremonies relating to ritual cleansing</h2>\n<p><strong><a href=\"https://ref.ly/Exod30:18-Exod30:20\">EXO 30:18–30:20</a></strong> <em>See also</em> <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Lev14:14-Lev14:18\">LEV 14:14–14:18</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Lev16:26\">LEV 16:26</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Lev22:6\">LEV 22:6</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Num19:7\">NUM 19:7</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Heb9:10\">HEB 9:10</a> <em>Many aspects of ritual activity were added to the biblical ones in Jewish laws and regulations.</em></p>\n<h2>Ceremonies relating to atonement</h2>\n<p><strong><a href=\"https://ref.ly/Lev17:11\">LEV 17:11</a></strong> <em>See also</em> <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Lev4:20\">LEV 4:20</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Lev8:30-Lev8:35\">LEV 8:30–8:35</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Lev16:10\">LEV 16:10</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Heb5:1\">HEB 5:1</a></p>\n<h2>Ceremonies conveying spiritual realities</h2>\n<h3>Passover: a ceremony symbolising salvation history</h3>\n<p><strong><a href=\"https://ref.ly/Luke22:15-Luke22:16\">LUK 22:15–22:16</a></strong> <em>See also</em> <a href=\"https://ref.ly/2Kgs23:21-2Kgs23:22\">2KI 23:21–23:22</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Ezra6:21-Ezra6:22\">EZR 6:21–6:22</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Matt26:17\">MAT 26:17</a> parallels <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Mark14:12\">MRK 14:12</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Luke22:7-Luke22:9\">LUK 22:7–22:9</a></p>\n<h3>Baptism: a ceremony symbolising new birth</h3>\n<p><strong><a href=\"https://ref.ly/John3:5\">JHN 3:5</a></strong> <em>See also</em> <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Acts10:48\">ACT 10:48</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Acts22:16\">ACT 22:16</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Gal3:27\">GAL 3:27</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Col2:12\">COL 2:12</a></p>\n<h3>Marriage: a ceremony symbolising faithful partnership</h3>\n<p><a href=\"https://ref.ly/Matt19:6\">MAT 19:6</a> parallel <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Mark10:9\">MRK 10:9</a>; ; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Eph5:25-Eph5:28\">EPH 5:25–5:28</a>; ; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Heb13:4\">HEB 13:4</a>; ; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Rev19:7\">REV 19:7</a></p>\n<h2>Ceremonies which lapsed into hypocrisy</h2>\n<h3>Washing ceremonies without accompanying inner cleanliness</h3>\n<p><strong><a href=\"https://ref.ly/Matt23:25\">MAT 23:25</a></strong> <em>See also</em> <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Matt23:27-Matt23:28\">MAT 23:27–23:28</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Mark7:4\">MRK 7:4</a></p>\n<h3>Sacrificial ceremonies without inner repentance</h3>\n<p><strong><a href=\"https://ref.ly/Amos5:21-Amos5:22\">AMO 5:21–5:22</a></strong> <em>See also</em> <a href=\"https://ref.ly/1Sam15:22\">1SA 15:22</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Ps51:16-Ps51:17\">PSA 51:16–51:17</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Isa1:11-Isa1:17\">ISA 1:11–1:17</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Hos8:11-Hos8:13\">HOS 8:11–8:13</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Mal1:8\">MAL 1:8</a></p>\n<h3>Initiation ceremonies without real commitment</h3>\n<p><strong><a href=\"https://ref.ly/1Cor7:19\">1CO 7:19</a></strong> <em>See also</em> <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Acts15:1\">ACT 15:1</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Acts15:8-Acts15:10\">ACT 15:8–15:10</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Rom2:28-Rom2:29\">ROM 2:28–2:29</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Gal5:6\">GAL 5:6</a></p>\n<h2>Jesus Christ brings freedom from meaningless ceremonies</h2>\n<p><strong><a href=\"https://ref.ly/Gal5:1\">GAL 5:1</a></strong> <em>See also</em> <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Gal4:8-Gal4:10\">GAL 4:8–4:10</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Eph2:14-Eph2:18\">EPH 2:14–2:18</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Col2:13-Col2:23\">COL 2:13–2:23</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Heb7:18-Heb7:19\">HEB 7:18–7:19</a></p>",
